comment.narrative:
1. (2) The OPC convened a PSC meeting on the 18th of January 2017 to review and adopt 2017 Annual Work Plan. In addition, through the coordination role of the OPC, a joint PSC field visit was organized in Mudzi/Mutoko from March 20-24th 2017.
2.a	The NPRC identified four pillars for capacity enhancement efforts in 2017. The learning programmes for these capacity enhancement retreats were refined with the assistance of technical experts.
2.b  The NPRC Bill was presented to Parliament in February, and was then subjected to public hearings throughout the country;
2.c  Preparatory work for the designing the ToRs to support the development of internal tools and systems for the NPRC is underway;
3.a.	For the first Quarter, 1 dialogue was held to review and validate the peace mascot - a prototype leveraging on the role of the creative arts and culture sector to foster reconciliation and promote peace; 
3.b  No progress was recorded for this Quarter, while preliminary engagement with UN Women is underway to support capacity strengthening of women in mediation and negotiation skills. 
4.a  The programme's community capacity for peace component only resumed in April 2017. In this quarter and through the coordination of the IP a Joint Monitoring Visit to LPCs in Mutoko and Mudzi was coordinated.
4.b  2.	To improve the quality of conflict and mediation services offered by communities a tailored information gathering and reporting system was developed collaboratively with 25 local facilitators. This system will be piloted in the 2nd quarter.
